Activation-induced markers were quantified via flow cytometry (FACSLyric, BD Biosciences). A surface staining on PBMC was performed with anti-CD3      (BD, clone SK7), anti-CD4      (BD, clone L200), anti-CD8      (DAKO, clone DK25), anti-CD45RA      (BD, clone L48), anti-CCR7      (R&D Systems, clone 150503), anti-CD69      (BD, clone FN50) and anti-CD137      (Miltenyi, clone 4B4-1). T-cell subsets were identified via the following gating strategy: LIVE CD3      were selected and divided in CD3      CD4      and CD3      CD8      . Within the CD4 and CD8 subsets, memory subsets were gated as CD45RA      CCR7      (naive, T

 N

), CD45RA      , CCR7      (central memory, T

 CM

), CD45RA      CCR7      (effector memory, T

 EM

) or CD45RA      CCR7      (terminally differentiated effectors, T

 EMRA

). T cells specifically activated by SARS-CoV-2 were identified by up-regulation of CD69 and CD137. An average of 500,000 cells was always acquired, the gating strategy is schematically represented in (Fig. S1A-J). In analysis, PBMC stimulated with MP_CD8_A and MP_CD8_B were concatenated and analyzed as a single file for SARS-CoV-2-specific responses to MP_CD8.
